WEBVTT

00:00:11.116 --> 00:00:15.078
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

00:00:41.521 --> 00:00:44.941
<i>Things suddenly took a strange turn</i>
<i>after he got a call.</i>

00:01:42.540 --> 00:01:43.541
Se-yun?

00:01:45.752 --> 00:01:47.337
Se-yun!

00:01:47.420 --> 00:01:49.214
<i>And it turned into a chase.</i>

00:01:49.297 --> 00:01:50.340
Hey, stop!

00:02:04.520 --> 00:02:05.730
Mrs. Ahn?

00:02:07.482 --> 00:02:08.358
What are you…

00:02:17.450 --> 00:02:18.409
It was Eun-joo?

00:02:22.664 --> 00:02:23.873
It was dear Eun-joo?

00:02:28.878 --> 00:02:30.004
How could that…

00:02:30.755 --> 00:02:32.382
But the real shocker

00:02:33.258 --> 00:02:35.260
is that she knows more than anyone.

00:02:35.343 --> 00:02:37.595
The woman who we thought knew nothing!

00:02:38.513 --> 00:02:39.889
Why are you here?

00:02:42.850 --> 00:02:44.269
Did you follow me?

00:02:45.561 --> 00:02:47.897
No, I thought you were Se-yun.

00:02:50.733 --> 00:02:51.985
Why are <i>you </i>here, Mrs. Ahn?

00:02:53.444 --> 00:02:54.529
Se-yun?

00:02:56.781 --> 00:02:58.908
So you're the young man
who went to the hotel?

00:02:59.575 --> 00:03:01.452
The one who asked if it was a murder?

00:03:05.707 --> 00:03:06.708
You

00:03:08.501 --> 00:03:09.669
went to the hotel too?

00:03:17.135 --> 00:03:20.847
If you went to the hotel, you'll know.
It was just an accident.

00:03:20.930 --> 00:03:23.933
And this is a family matter.
It's none of your business!

00:03:24.434 --> 00:03:27.020
How can it be none of my business?
A person died.

00:03:27.520 --> 00:03:29.772
You know it wasn't an accident,
as the letter said.

00:03:34.235 --> 00:03:36.321
"I have the hospital CCTV footage."

00:03:38.990 --> 00:03:40.116
That letter.

00:03:42.201 --> 00:03:43.786
How much do you…

00:03:49.042 --> 00:03:50.335
What do you want?

00:03:51.002 --> 00:03:54.255
No, I don't want a thing. Don't worry.

00:03:54.339 --> 00:03:55.465
I just…

00:03:56.716 --> 00:03:59.177
I just want to know the truth. That's all.

00:04:01.262 --> 00:04:03.222
And I'm on <i>your </i>side.

00:04:04.474 --> 00:04:05.475
Not the police's.

00:04:08.478 --> 00:04:09.395
The police?

00:04:10.897 --> 00:04:13.149
If you won't tell me,
I have no other choice.

00:04:14.650 --> 00:04:16.611
To uncover the truth about her death.

00:04:20.782 --> 00:04:22.075
<i>In the end,</i>

00:04:22.825 --> 00:04:24.494
<i>she told me everything.</i>

00:04:26.621 --> 00:04:29.749
Everything she said was so shocking.
That's why I'm late.

00:04:29.832 --> 00:04:33.169
-I couldn't interrupt her. That's why I--
-Okay.

00:04:37.799 --> 00:04:38.966
I see.

00:04:39.592 --> 00:04:41.219
Okay. Calm down.

00:04:41.886 --> 00:04:44.430
Let's sit down first, and you can tell me.

00:04:48.851 --> 00:04:52.146
Now tell me everything you heard today.

00:04:52.980 --> 00:04:55.024
Don't leave anything out.

00:04:55.108 --> 00:04:56.109
All right.

00:04:57.068 --> 00:04:58.611
The story starts with--

00:04:58.694 --> 00:04:59.821
Wait, hold on.

00:05:23.636 --> 00:05:24.470
From now on…

00:05:26.431 --> 00:05:28.099
talk quietly. Softly.

00:05:28.850 --> 00:05:29.934
Okay, so…

00:05:40.486 --> 00:05:41.487
Yes, hello?

00:05:46.909 --> 00:05:47.869
Really?

00:05:49.328 --> 00:05:50.329
Okay.

00:05:51.664 --> 00:05:52.582
Yes, I understand.

00:05:53.583 --> 00:05:54.625
I'll head there now.

00:05:55.126 --> 00:05:57.170
Hey, what are you doing?

00:05:57.253 --> 00:05:58.087
What is it?

00:05:59.505 --> 00:06:02.383
I'm sorry.
I have something urgent to take care of.

00:06:03.718 --> 00:06:06.095
I'll call you later… no, tomorrow.

00:06:06.179 --> 00:06:07.805
Wait, tomorrow? Why?

00:06:07.889 --> 00:06:09.682
What is it?

00:06:10.266 --> 00:06:12.059
Did something happen to Eun-joo?

00:06:12.143 --> 00:06:13.561
Well? What is it?

00:06:13.644 --> 00:06:17.482
No, it doesn't concern Mrs. Ahn, but…

00:06:18.107 --> 00:06:20.234
Hey, you can't just leave like this!

00:06:20.318 --> 00:06:21.277
Wait.

00:06:22.361 --> 00:06:23.321
Lee Kang.

00:06:23.821 --> 00:06:24.739
Call me.

00:06:25.823 --> 00:06:27.450
Soon. Call as soon as you can!

00:06:36.709 --> 00:06:38.211
So when it comes to

00:06:39.504 --> 00:06:40.463
literary incidents,

00:06:41.422 --> 00:06:43.841
it's not the incident itself that matters.

00:06:48.304 --> 00:06:50.640
Rather, the focus is on

00:06:51.974 --> 00:06:55.978
what kind of person
gets caught up in said incident

00:06:56.479 --> 00:06:58.856
and what is revealed
about their character.

00:07:04.278 --> 00:07:06.239
You little punk. Where are you?

00:07:10.368 --> 00:07:14.413
Why haven't you called?
And why weren't you in…

00:07:14.497 --> 00:07:15.414
Hello.

00:07:15.498 --> 00:07:20.253
Why weren't you in class?
Call me as soon as you hear this, okay?

00:07:22.338 --> 00:07:23.172
Hey, Kim Se-yun!

00:07:30.555 --> 00:07:31.389
Do you…

00:07:32.056 --> 00:07:33.015
Yes, Professor?

00:07:34.350 --> 00:07:35.226
Do you…

00:07:37.687 --> 00:07:39.021
Do you know where Lee…

00:07:45.236 --> 00:07:46.612
Never mind.

00:07:47.405 --> 00:07:48.239
You can go.

00:08:04.130 --> 00:08:06.674
If you have any ideas

00:08:07.508 --> 00:08:10.261
for new general education
elective courses,

00:08:10.761 --> 00:08:12.722
now's a great time to share them.

00:08:14.515 --> 00:08:17.435
The university administration
has asked us to add

00:08:17.518 --> 00:08:19.729
more unique general education courses.

00:08:20.229 --> 00:08:21.230
Department Chair?

00:08:22.064 --> 00:08:23.816
LEE KANG

00:08:30.114 --> 00:08:31.115
Hey.

00:08:31.198 --> 00:08:34.368
<i>I'm sorry, Mr. Heo.</i>
<i>I should have called sooner.</i>

00:08:34.952 --> 00:08:36.078
<i>Were you asleep?</i>

00:08:36.621 --> 00:08:37.955
No, go ahead.

00:08:39.206 --> 00:08:41.626
<i>Are you mad</i>
<i>because I didn't answer your calls?</i>

00:08:42.126 --> 00:08:43.919
No, just talk.

00:08:44.462 --> 00:08:45.504
What happened?

00:08:48.299 --> 00:08:50.259
<i>It's a pretty long story.</i>

00:08:51.135 --> 00:08:52.303
<i>The call I got yesterday</i>

00:08:53.804 --> 00:08:55.389
<i>was from the nursing home.</i>

00:08:57.183 --> 00:09:00.561
You know about my dad being here
from my assignment, right?

00:09:01.771 --> 00:09:04.106
Anyway, they called to say
he'd gone missing,

00:09:04.774 --> 00:09:05.983
so I'm out of town.

00:09:08.402 --> 00:09:09.362
What, out of town?

00:09:09.445 --> 00:09:12.156
Yes, it's actually quite far.

00:09:22.333 --> 00:09:25.586
We found him, thankfully,
so you don't have to worry, but

00:09:26.962 --> 00:09:29.882
<i>my dad's a little hurt.</i>

00:09:31.258 --> 00:09:32.968
<i>I'll have to stay here for a while.</i>

00:09:33.052 --> 00:09:34.804
Hey, then what about our conversation?

00:09:36.847 --> 00:09:37.682
Sorry?

00:09:39.934 --> 00:09:40.768
Right, yeah.

00:09:42.019 --> 00:09:45.272
How's your father? Is he doing okay?

00:09:45.773 --> 00:09:49.360
You mentioned that he struggles
with alcoholism, didn't you?

00:09:49.443 --> 00:09:50.569
<i>Yes, that's right.</i>

00:09:51.529 --> 00:09:52.363
<i>You remember.</i>

00:09:52.988 --> 00:09:55.074
Of course I remember.

00:09:55.574 --> 00:09:57.284
I hope he gets better soon.

00:09:58.119 --> 00:09:59.036
But…

00:10:00.121 --> 00:10:03.499
Hey, what are we going to do
about our conversation?

00:10:04.250 --> 00:10:07.795
Is it possible for you to write it up
as your assignment?

00:10:11.590 --> 00:10:12.633
Assignment?

00:10:15.511 --> 00:10:18.264
I had to rush here,
so I couldn't bring my laptop.

00:10:19.098 --> 00:10:21.809
Or we could do it over the phone.
Let's do that.

00:10:21.892 --> 00:10:23.561
I'm free now. I have time.

00:10:23.644 --> 00:10:25.604
<i>No, I can't talk for long.</i>

00:10:30.484 --> 00:10:31.485
Okay, then.

00:10:32.153 --> 00:10:34.822
I'll try to borrow the computer
at the nursing home office.

00:10:35.531 --> 00:10:38.242
I can't finish it in one go,
but I'll try whenever I can.

00:10:38.325 --> 00:10:39.577
It might take about a week.

00:10:40.703 --> 00:10:42.037
What, a week?

00:10:42.121 --> 00:10:43.456
<i>Kang!</i>

00:10:43.956 --> 00:10:45.040
<i>I have to go.</i>

00:10:45.124 --> 00:10:47.418
<i>My dad keeps asking for me.</i>
<i>I'll email you soon.</i>

00:10:47.501 --> 00:10:49.253
Hey, Lee Kang! Wait!

00:10:51.547 --> 00:10:52.715
You bastard!

00:10:56.385 --> 00:10:57.636
What? A week?

00:11:01.015 --> 00:11:02.224
A whole week?

00:11:14.320 --> 00:11:18.407
He said he'd email me soon.
When exactly is "soon"?

00:11:19.492 --> 00:11:21.410
That little bastard.

00:11:27.374 --> 00:11:29.710
What the hell's with <i>this </i>bastard?

00:11:30.294 --> 00:11:33.214
Bastard drives like a goddamn maniac.

00:11:33.297 --> 00:11:34.507
Choi Dong-ju.

00:11:34.590 --> 00:11:35.424
Here.

00:11:38.511 --> 00:11:39.428
Choi Mi-gyeong.

00:11:39.512 --> 00:11:40.346
Here.

00:11:50.356 --> 00:11:53.192
<i>Mr. Heo.</i>
<i>I just sent you my first assignment.</i>

00:11:53.776 --> 00:11:56.695
<i>I tried to write down</i>
<i>what Mrs. Ahn told me, word for word.</i>

00:11:57.279 --> 00:11:58.405
<i>Brace yourself.</i>

00:12:04.328 --> 00:12:05.996
-Choi Bo-geom.
-Here.

00:12:13.963 --> 00:12:14.880
Well…

00:12:16.465 --> 00:12:19.969
I'm sorry, but today's class is canceled.

00:12:21.011 --> 00:12:23.305
I'll make up for this class next time.

00:12:24.807 --> 00:12:25.683
Sorry?

00:12:25.766 --> 00:12:26.809
Class is…

00:12:26.892 --> 00:12:28.018
Canceled? Seriously?

00:12:28.102 --> 00:12:29.770
What's gotten into the old fart?

00:12:30.521 --> 00:12:32.314
Let's go to an Internet café and chill.

00:12:41.448 --> 00:12:42.658
Professor, hello.

00:12:42.741 --> 00:12:45.661
When can you send
the exam questions for finals?

00:12:45.744 --> 00:12:46.579
Professor?

00:12:48.581 --> 00:12:49.415
What the heck?

00:12:49.999 --> 00:12:52.126
-Hello, sir.
-What's up with him lately?

00:13:11.645 --> 00:13:15.357
<i>Actually, I've known for a long time</i>

00:13:16.066 --> 00:13:18.444
<i>that my husband was cheating on me.</i>

00:13:18.944 --> 00:13:20.321
<i>How could I not know?</i>

00:13:22.615 --> 00:13:23.824
But

00:13:25.034 --> 00:13:27.369
I've never brought it up and asked him.

00:13:27.870 --> 00:13:30.122
My pride wouldn't let me.

00:13:31.790 --> 00:13:33.208
I can't forgive him.

00:13:36.670 --> 00:13:39.423
But I thought I could play dumb

00:13:40.758 --> 00:13:42.426
to protect my children.

00:13:43.928 --> 00:13:45.346
So I just put up with it.

00:13:46.138 --> 00:13:47.431
Endured it.

00:13:50.559 --> 00:13:51.685
But

00:13:53.145 --> 00:13:55.689
I couldn't just let it slide this time.

00:13:58.525 --> 00:14:00.694
In my home, of all places.

00:14:05.199 --> 00:14:07.660
In our own home, where my babies live.

00:14:11.121 --> 00:14:13.874
With the likes of
that worthless housekeeper.

00:15:45.174 --> 00:15:46.842
HAPPY TIME
PREGNANCY TEST KIT

00:16:24.755 --> 00:16:25.714
What are you doing?

00:16:29.093 --> 00:16:30.886
What is this, Min-hui?

00:16:31.470 --> 00:16:32.888
What's this doing here?

00:16:34.598 --> 00:16:35.516
Why is that…

00:16:41.271 --> 00:16:42.981
How would I know?

00:17:01.375 --> 00:17:05.379
You're still awake. What's wrong?
Should I turn off the lights?

00:17:06.797 --> 00:17:08.173
No, it's okay.

00:17:13.095 --> 00:17:14.096
What is it?

00:17:16.014 --> 00:17:17.724
Are you still upset over her?

00:17:18.225 --> 00:17:19.977
The fight you had earlier today?

00:17:21.103 --> 00:17:22.104
I don't know.

00:17:24.648 --> 00:17:26.441
It's bringing back memories.

00:17:27.442 --> 00:17:28.694
Min-hui

00:17:29.736 --> 00:17:31.780
used to wear my clothes without asking.

00:17:32.990 --> 00:17:34.449
Bringing that up again?

00:17:34.950 --> 00:17:38.704
You were going to donate them anyway,
so what's the big deal?

00:17:41.623 --> 00:17:43.041
Then what about the scarf?

00:17:44.209 --> 00:17:45.502
Why'd she steal what's mine?

00:17:46.170 --> 00:17:50.716
She said she never stole it
when I followed her out and asked.

00:17:50.799 --> 00:17:52.676
Maybe you were mistaken.

00:17:53.302 --> 00:17:54.344
Mistaken?

00:17:56.388 --> 00:17:59.516
Are you taking her side right now?

00:18:00.225 --> 00:18:01.935
<i>I couldn't stand it.</i>

00:18:02.603 --> 00:18:05.063
<i>I had to put an end to it</i>
<i>before Yun found out.</i>

00:18:22.331 --> 00:18:24.666
What brings you here, on a weekend,

00:18:26.418 --> 00:18:28.212
to a shabby neighborhood like this?

00:18:34.092 --> 00:18:36.011
Here to apologize or something?

00:18:41.850 --> 00:18:42.684
Why do you…

00:18:45.395 --> 00:18:47.606
I found it in your bag yesterday.

00:18:48.649 --> 00:18:50.817
I am aware of what this means.

00:18:52.736 --> 00:18:53.570
What it means?

00:18:56.865 --> 00:18:58.116
Seriously?

00:18:58.617 --> 00:19:00.160
So you think

00:19:01.119 --> 00:19:03.288
I'm pregnant
with your husband's baby, lady?

00:19:03.372 --> 00:19:04.206
What?

00:19:04.957 --> 00:19:05.916
"Lady"?

00:19:06.833 --> 00:19:08.877
It looks like I'll be fired anyway.

00:19:09.628 --> 00:19:12.339
Are you saying
I should call you "ma'am" even here?

00:19:15.008 --> 00:19:15.842
Fine.

00:19:17.970 --> 00:19:19.304
Call me whatever you want.

00:19:19.888 --> 00:19:21.014
But this…

00:19:24.643 --> 00:19:26.478
What is it that you want?

00:19:37.656 --> 00:19:39.032
Look, lady.

00:19:39.658 --> 00:19:41.952
No, you've got it all wrong.

00:19:42.911 --> 00:19:43.870
Ridiculous.

00:19:45.789 --> 00:19:46.915
You're crazy.

00:19:47.416 --> 00:19:48.959
Completely insane.

00:19:52.838 --> 00:19:53.922
Listen up,

00:19:54.506 --> 00:19:55.799
lady.

00:19:57.968 --> 00:19:59.177
This

00:20:00.095 --> 00:20:03.015
has nothing to do
with your husband whatsoever.

00:20:04.182 --> 00:20:05.726
This is my private life.

00:20:07.185 --> 00:20:09.354
What do you take me for?

00:20:12.232 --> 00:20:13.358
Sure.

00:20:14.151 --> 00:20:17.404
It would be nice to snare a rich guy
with something like this.

00:20:18.488 --> 00:20:20.282
But not your husband.

00:20:22.326 --> 00:20:25.537
Think I'm mad enough to mess around
with a vile bastard like him?

00:20:26.121 --> 00:20:29.166
Think I'm like the bitches
he fools around with behind your back?

00:20:30.792 --> 00:20:33.337
Who do you think he is?
You really think he's all that?

00:20:34.963 --> 00:20:36.089
Don't be stupid.

00:20:37.382 --> 00:20:40.135
That husband of yours
is just a revolting hypocrite,

00:20:40.218 --> 00:20:42.137
a thief who's fooling the world…

00:20:45.223 --> 00:20:47.809
and a fucking loser.

00:20:49.811 --> 00:20:51.396
You don't even know a thing.

00:20:52.856 --> 00:20:54.358
What? Thief?

00:20:55.692 --> 00:20:56.985
What do you mean…

00:21:05.619 --> 00:21:08.080
<i>What she told me was so shocking.</i>

00:21:08.622 --> 00:21:10.582
<i>A secret of my husband's</i>

00:21:11.166 --> 00:21:12.959
<i>that I could never have imagined.</i>

00:21:15.670 --> 00:21:16.755
TO BE CONTINUED..

00:21:18.924 --> 00:21:21.843
Continued. To be continued.
It's always "to be continued.."!

00:21:23.720 --> 00:21:24.721
Unbelievable.

00:21:47.494 --> 00:21:48.412
Did you know…

00:21:52.165 --> 00:21:54.709
Hyeong-jong's book launch is
the day after tomorrow?

00:21:55.293 --> 00:21:56.503
Seong-hui called.

00:21:57.003 --> 00:21:57.838
Yeah.

00:21:58.630 --> 00:22:01.842
I called Professor Park to say
I can't make it. You can go by yourself.

00:22:03.552 --> 00:22:05.470
I hear Kim Su-hun will be there.

00:22:16.106 --> 00:22:19.151
And what exactly did Kim Su-hun steal?

00:22:19.651 --> 00:22:21.945
What theft did he commit, exactly?

00:22:26.825 --> 00:22:30.454
Yes, I know that you're busy
and have your hands full.

00:22:30.954 --> 00:22:34.749
So just tell me that first.
There's a reason I need to know now.

00:22:36.710 --> 00:22:37.627
Hey, Lee Kang.

00:22:38.336 --> 00:22:39.171
Lee Kang?

00:22:42.757 --> 00:22:44.843
That little shit.

00:23:00.609 --> 00:23:01.568
So,

00:23:02.903 --> 00:23:04.613
that theft he committed…

00:23:08.366 --> 00:23:09.701
There's no way.

00:23:15.081 --> 00:23:16.833
I have an older sister.

00:23:17.542 --> 00:23:18.793
I mean, "had."

00:23:20.045 --> 00:23:22.506
She was the only family member
I was attached to,

00:23:23.965 --> 00:23:25.634
but she died of cancer last year.

00:23:29.054 --> 00:23:31.431
I only found out after her funeral

00:23:32.599 --> 00:23:33.850
that her dream…

00:23:36.228 --> 00:23:37.646
was to become a writer.

00:23:46.154 --> 00:23:48.198
SHOULD I TELL MIN-HUI ABOUT MY DIAGNOSIS?

00:23:48.281 --> 00:23:50.325
THE DAY I FINISH THIS NOVEL,
I'LL BE CURED

00:24:06.675 --> 00:24:09.386
GUESTS AFTER DARK
SEON EUN-HUI

00:24:15.809 --> 00:24:17.352
Mom, what are you reading?

00:24:18.436 --> 00:24:19.271
What?

00:24:20.063 --> 00:24:22.732
Just something your aunt wrote.

00:24:24.442 --> 00:24:27.445
I always cursed her out
for shutting herself up in her room.

00:24:27.946 --> 00:24:29.573
Guess she was writing this crap.

00:24:31.241 --> 00:24:32.826
Still, it must be good.

00:24:33.785 --> 00:24:35.870
I've never seen you read anything before.

00:24:38.748 --> 00:24:39.583
Sweetheart.

00:24:41.876 --> 00:24:44.796
Should I try to send this to a publisher?

00:24:45.297 --> 00:24:46.798
Publishers print books, right?

00:24:47.841 --> 00:24:48.675
Books?

00:24:49.509 --> 00:24:51.261
It might make us some money.

00:24:51.761 --> 00:24:54.431
Then I could pay
for my smart girl's education

00:24:54.931 --> 00:24:56.141
and open a hair salon.

00:24:56.808 --> 00:24:58.226
Sure, try sending it.

00:24:59.019 --> 00:25:02.230
You said the man you work for
makes a ton of money, too, right?

00:25:31.801 --> 00:25:34.262
Mr. Kim, sorry to interrupt.

00:25:35.263 --> 00:25:37.891
The manuscript I gave you last time.

00:25:38.391 --> 00:25:39.643
Did you read it?

00:25:40.560 --> 00:25:43.229
I've been waiting,
but you haven't said anything about it.

00:25:44.272 --> 00:25:45.398
About what?

00:25:46.941 --> 00:25:49.986
You know, the thing I gave you last time.
My sister's novel.

00:25:50.070 --> 00:25:51.863
I asked if you could read it.

00:25:57.035 --> 00:25:57.869
That.

00:25:59.037 --> 00:26:00.038
I'm sorry.

00:26:01.831 --> 00:26:03.583
My book's coming out soon,

00:26:04.250 --> 00:26:06.961
so I don't have time
to read someone's rough draft.

00:26:10.965 --> 00:26:11.800
Okay.

00:26:12.300 --> 00:26:15.345
And you don't have to clean
when I'm working.

00:26:16.471 --> 00:26:18.682
I thought I told you last time.

00:26:30.318 --> 00:26:32.529
Then could I have it back?

00:26:33.279 --> 00:26:35.323
I was going to send it to a publisher.

00:26:37.409 --> 00:26:38.618
Well,

00:26:39.327 --> 00:26:41.121
it should be around here somewhere.

00:26:41.621 --> 00:26:43.039
Where did I put it again?

00:26:44.457 --> 00:26:45.500
That's

00:26:46.501 --> 00:26:48.920
the only copy of the manuscript.

00:26:54.884 --> 00:26:56.177
All right.

00:26:56.970 --> 00:26:58.847
I'll find it and give it back to you.

00:27:08.815 --> 00:27:12.569
<i>I only found out</i>
<i>after your husband's book was published.</i>

00:27:14.487 --> 00:27:15.321
Wait.

00:27:24.998 --> 00:27:27.083
What the fuck is this?

00:27:30.587 --> 00:27:31.629
EYES OF THE HOUSE

00:27:33.882 --> 00:27:36.217
I don't know what you're talking about.

00:27:37.594 --> 00:27:38.887
How are the two the same?

00:27:39.554 --> 00:27:41.139
Do you think I'm an idiot?

00:27:43.433 --> 00:27:45.226
A poor woman with no home…

00:27:46.352 --> 00:27:48.855
So, a woman who likes
looking around people's homes

00:27:48.938 --> 00:27:51.691
sneaks into a rich couple's house
while they're on vacation

00:27:51.775 --> 00:27:53.777
and secretly stays there. That's the same.

00:27:54.778 --> 00:27:58.656
And here. The part where she finds
a body in the fridge is also the same.

00:27:58.740 --> 00:27:59.824
Lady.

00:28:00.950 --> 00:28:01.993
Lady?

00:28:03.578 --> 00:28:05.705
Lady, what are you saying?

00:28:06.331 --> 00:28:08.458
Such a claim could get you in big trouble.

00:28:09.793 --> 00:28:11.419
What do you know about literature?

00:28:12.629 --> 00:28:14.756
Do you even know what a story is?

00:28:15.715 --> 00:28:18.384
If you keep making
such baseless accusations,

00:28:18.885 --> 00:28:20.553
you'll have to face legal action.

00:28:23.181 --> 00:28:25.850
I don't fucking care. Cut the bullshit!

00:28:27.519 --> 00:28:29.646
You think I'll just let this slide?

00:28:29.729 --> 00:28:31.898
You really don't get it.

00:28:33.274 --> 00:28:35.652
Do you have any proof
that I plagiarized her work?

00:28:36.653 --> 00:28:37.487
Proof?

00:28:37.987 --> 00:28:38.822
Yeah.

00:28:40.573 --> 00:28:43.493
Without proof,
who do you think would believe you?

00:28:46.830 --> 00:28:47.789
I have it.

00:28:48.289 --> 00:28:49.249
Proof.

00:28:55.171 --> 00:28:56.631
My sister's novel.

00:28:59.384 --> 00:29:01.010
I have the original file.

00:29:09.185 --> 00:29:10.436
<i>From that day on,</i>

00:29:10.937 --> 00:29:13.606
<i>your husband was totally at my mercy.</i>

00:29:39.048 --> 00:29:42.302
<i>One word from me</i>
<i>could ruin his whole life.</i>

00:29:42.844 --> 00:29:44.721
<i>A pathetic little fucker.</i>

00:29:48.558 --> 00:29:49.601
This is epic!

00:29:51.978 --> 00:29:55.565
Wow, is this honestly real? Is it?

00:29:57.275 --> 00:29:59.110
She called him a pathetic little fucker.

00:30:01.779 --> 00:30:05.199
He really is completely insane, isn't he?

00:30:06.326 --> 00:30:08.119
Mr. Kim Su-hun.

00:30:08.202 --> 00:30:10.246
Kim Su-hun. Hey, Su-hun!

00:30:10.747 --> 00:30:16.210
How could an esteemed author like you
steal someone else's novel?

00:30:16.294 --> 00:30:18.880
You crazy son of a bitch,
you fucking nutjob.

00:30:18.963 --> 00:30:22.050
So that's all you were, huh?

00:30:26.679 --> 00:30:28.473
All right, you son of a bitch.

00:30:29.349 --> 00:30:31.643
Let me see

00:30:32.393 --> 00:30:33.895
just how shameless you are.

00:30:39.943 --> 00:30:43.696
Hey, it's me. I'm going.
I'll attend the thing.

00:30:45.990 --> 00:30:47.450
What are you talking about?

00:30:47.533 --> 00:30:49.994
<i>I'll attend Professor Park's book launch.</i>

00:30:54.999 --> 00:30:56.209
Why all of a sudden?

00:30:59.170 --> 00:31:00.380
I guess you found out.

00:31:01.631 --> 00:31:05.343
Found out what?
What are you talking about?

00:31:05.426 --> 00:31:08.554
<i>Kim Su-hun's wife.</i>
<i>She's going to be there too.</i>

00:31:09.639 --> 00:31:11.391
<i>Isn't that what changed your mind?</i>

00:31:15.061 --> 00:31:17.271
Why didn't you tell me this earlier?

00:31:18.690 --> 00:31:20.274
I suggested that she be invited.

00:31:21.609 --> 00:31:22.860
You did? Why?

00:31:23.903 --> 00:31:26.239
I just wanted to see
what kind of woman she is.

00:31:26.322 --> 00:31:29.158
<i>Why would you meet Eun-joo?</i>
<i>What are you planning to do?</i>

00:31:31.494 --> 00:31:33.746
<i>She's going through a hard time right now.</i>

00:31:34.288 --> 00:31:36.332
<i>She has a lot on her mind.</i>

00:32:05.319 --> 00:32:07.196
<i>No, you're lying.</i>

00:32:08.531 --> 00:32:10.575
He'd never do something like that.

00:32:11.451 --> 00:32:13.745
Do you know how many books he's written?

00:32:14.495 --> 00:32:15.455
How could he…

00:32:17.498 --> 00:32:19.208
steal someone's work like that?

00:32:20.501 --> 00:32:22.086
For fuck's sake.

00:32:23.504 --> 00:32:24.338
Look.

00:32:25.590 --> 00:32:28.342
Are you having trouble believing,
or do you just not want to?

00:32:32.263 --> 00:32:33.097
See this?

00:32:35.099 --> 00:32:38.102
That bastard nearly killed me yesterday.

00:33:12.053 --> 00:33:13.221
Is that true?

00:33:14.388 --> 00:33:15.348
What?

00:33:17.308 --> 00:33:19.227
That you have the original file.

00:33:19.894 --> 00:33:24.982
Fucking hell.
If you don't want to believe me, don't.

00:33:25.900 --> 00:33:27.819
I can just upload it online.

00:33:28.694 --> 00:33:30.279
Then give it to me.

00:33:30.780 --> 00:33:31.614
Sell it to me.

00:33:52.343 --> 00:33:53.469
Would this be enough?

00:34:13.489 --> 00:34:16.409
If I'd known this would happen,
I'd have told you sooner.

00:34:18.327 --> 00:34:19.996
Now we're talking.

00:34:21.038 --> 00:34:22.290
That bastard

00:34:23.082 --> 00:34:24.417
was way too stingy.

00:34:29.881 --> 00:34:31.757
Bring it to work with you on Monday.

00:34:33.968 --> 00:34:35.887
I'll have the money ready.

00:35:08.419 --> 00:35:10.046
Yes, hello?

00:35:11.005 --> 00:35:11.839
Excuse me?

00:35:12.548 --> 00:35:13.716
The police?

00:35:14.550 --> 00:35:16.802
<i>In the end, she never made it to work</i>

00:35:17.637 --> 00:35:19.472
<i>because she died on Sunday night.</i>

00:35:23.809 --> 00:35:25.102
<i>After that day…</i>

00:35:26.938 --> 00:35:28.689
<i>many things changed.</i>

00:35:32.902 --> 00:35:34.904
<i>Was it really a car accident?</i>

00:35:36.030 --> 00:35:36.906
<i>What if</i>

00:35:38.574 --> 00:35:40.117
<i>her death wasn't an accident?</i>

00:35:57.593 --> 00:35:59.679
<i>I couldn't just sit around.</i>

00:36:00.846 --> 00:36:03.224
<i>I had to find out the truth</i>
<i>about her death.</i>

00:36:07.144 --> 00:36:07.979
A murder?

00:36:08.854 --> 00:36:11.065
<i>I was able to confirm</i>
<i>that it was a car accident,</i>

00:36:11.649 --> 00:36:13.985
<i>but it did nothing to ease the burden.</i>

00:36:14.068 --> 00:36:16.279
No, don't ask the church volunteer group.

00:36:17.822 --> 00:36:19.740
No? Why not?

00:36:19.824 --> 00:36:21.742
Fundraising or whatever…

00:36:23.661 --> 00:36:25.037
would take too long.

00:36:25.121 --> 00:36:27.456
The funeral should be held
as soon as possible.

00:36:29.166 --> 00:36:31.919
People might talk.

00:36:32.712 --> 00:36:35.298
That would be disrespectful
to the deceased.

00:36:36.340 --> 00:36:38.467
If money's the issue,
we can take care of it.

00:36:39.343 --> 00:36:40.386
I'll pay for it.

00:36:43.222 --> 00:36:44.390
You will?

00:36:46.017 --> 00:36:48.519
-Just run.
-What's your name? How old?

00:36:52.898 --> 00:36:54.608
<i>She's so mature for her age.</i>

00:36:54.692 --> 00:36:57.445
<i>It's almost concerning.</i>
<i>She doesn't even cry.</i>

00:36:58.654 --> 00:37:00.823
What will happen to her now?

00:37:01.324 --> 00:37:04.994
Luckily, we were able to get in touch
with her grandmother in the States.

00:37:05.077 --> 00:37:06.329
She leaves in two months.

00:37:08.289 --> 00:37:09.915
I'm relieved to hear

00:37:10.666 --> 00:37:12.376
she has family who'll take her in.

00:37:13.002 --> 00:37:16.130
I guess Eun-seo's mom
had one last bit of luck.

00:37:16.213 --> 00:37:17.631
She was able to have a funeral,

00:37:17.715 --> 00:37:19.759
albeit belatedly,
thanks to a friend like you.

00:37:20.593 --> 00:37:23.596
How did you say you knew her again?

00:37:26.807 --> 00:37:27.808
If you could

00:37:28.726 --> 00:37:31.979
use this money for the child's
travel expenses to the States…

00:37:35.733 --> 00:37:37.985
I was indebted to her.

00:37:38.694 --> 00:37:39.987
This is only part of it.

00:37:42.907 --> 00:37:43.866
Director?

00:37:44.784 --> 00:37:45.659
Yes?

00:37:46.327 --> 00:37:47.828
I solved all the questions.

00:38:03.219 --> 00:38:05.513
The funeral is tomorrow.

00:38:06.639 --> 00:38:08.682
Did you pick your mom's memorial portrait?

00:38:39.255 --> 00:38:41.799
It's okay. Don't cry.

00:38:43.509 --> 00:38:44.593
It's okay.

00:39:00.776 --> 00:39:02.820
Hey, Eun-seo, your mom…

00:39:05.239 --> 00:39:07.074
Did your mom…

00:39:09.452 --> 00:39:13.456
Did she, by any chance,

00:39:14.457 --> 00:39:16.083
have some sort of file?

00:39:17.710 --> 00:39:19.003
A USB?

00:39:33.476 --> 00:39:34.435
This?

00:39:38.230 --> 00:39:40.232
Mom said it was important

00:39:40.983 --> 00:39:43.027
and told me to keep it safe.

00:39:46.030 --> 00:39:47.698
The thing is, Eun-seo,

00:39:48.491 --> 00:39:49.909
this isn't actually

00:39:50.951 --> 00:39:51.785
your mom's.

00:39:56.248 --> 00:39:57.625
It's mine.

00:40:12.056 --> 00:40:14.308
<i>I was just like him.</i>

00:40:15.434 --> 00:40:17.436
<i>No different from my husband.</i>

00:40:18.187 --> 00:40:20.981
<i>A disgusting, revolting person.</i>

00:40:38.707 --> 00:40:42.503
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

00:40:42.586 --> 00:40:46.048
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

00:40:46.131 --> 00:40:50.261
<i>Happy birthday, dear Dad</i>

00:40:50.344 --> 00:40:52.221
<i>Happy birthday to you</i>

00:40:52.304 --> 00:40:54.014
A WONDERFUL HUSBAND, DEPENDABLE DAD

00:41:04.191 --> 00:41:05.901
This is where it ends.

00:41:07.945 --> 00:41:09.488
It's all over now.

00:41:19.290 --> 00:41:21.500
Happy birthday, Dad!

00:41:21.584 --> 00:41:23.836
Thanks, everyone.

00:41:23.919 --> 00:41:25.546
Thank you, honey.

00:41:25.629 --> 00:41:26.839
My goodness.

00:41:32.886 --> 00:41:35.889
TO BE CONTINUED..

00:41:46.775 --> 00:41:50.362
How does this make any sense?
How is this even possible?

00:41:52.448 --> 00:41:53.282
Look.

00:41:54.658 --> 00:41:58.537
She clearly knew what her husband did,

00:41:59.496 --> 00:42:03.083
so why would she get rid of the evidence
and even let him hug her?

00:42:03.584 --> 00:42:06.879
<i>Why are you getting mad at me?</i>
<i>I just wrote what I heard.</i>

00:42:06.962 --> 00:42:09.089
I'm not mad at you, you punk!

00:42:09.840 --> 00:42:13.927
It's just frustrating that she's covering
for her scumbag husband, goddammit!

00:42:14.428 --> 00:42:15.387
<i>Mr. Heo.</i>

00:42:16.180 --> 00:42:17.765
<i>Are you jealous?</i>

00:42:17.848 --> 00:42:18.974
What? Jealous?

00:42:19.850 --> 00:42:22.436
You little punk. How dare you!

00:42:27.983 --> 00:42:29.610
Let's take my car today.

00:42:32.029 --> 00:42:33.530
That top is almost see-through.

00:42:34.782 --> 00:42:36.200
You really dolled yourself up.

00:42:37.201 --> 00:42:39.203
You're the one who dolled yourself up.

00:42:39.745 --> 00:42:42.331
I guess you wanted to look sharp
for a certain someone.

00:42:53.300 --> 00:42:54.134
What's wrong?

00:42:55.302 --> 00:42:56.387
Stomach cramps.

00:42:57.554 --> 00:42:58.931
Since yesterday.

00:43:02.851 --> 00:43:04.103
Should I drive?

00:43:11.193 --> 00:43:12.152
Why don't you…

00:43:14.571 --> 00:43:15.781
just stay home today?

00:43:18.951 --> 00:43:19.785
What?

00:43:22.162 --> 00:43:25.708
Stomach cramps are no joke.
Go home and get some rest.

00:43:26.333 --> 00:43:28.001
I can go by myself.

00:43:30.713 --> 00:43:32.464
You don't want me to go, do you?

00:43:34.007 --> 00:43:35.092
Here you go again.

00:43:36.051 --> 00:43:39.430
I'm just worried about you, that's all.

00:43:39.972 --> 00:43:42.099
We're not getting any younger.

00:43:42.182 --> 00:43:45.728
We have to rest whenever we're sick.
That's the only answer.

00:43:51.567 --> 00:43:52.818
Fine.

00:43:54.403 --> 00:43:55.320
Go by yourself.

00:44:00.826 --> 00:44:02.119
Go. Go on.

00:44:08.751 --> 00:44:11.086
I'll be back soon. Go in and rest up.

00:44:11.170 --> 00:44:14.715
And if it gets worse, go see a doctor.

00:44:49.291 --> 00:44:52.336
We'll now hear from
Professor Park Hyeong-jong,

00:44:52.419 --> 00:44:54.797
the author of
<i>Designing a Sustainable Future</i>.

00:44:54.880 --> 00:44:56.548
Let's invite him on stage.

00:44:56.632 --> 00:44:58.801
A big round of applause, please.

00:45:01.678 --> 00:45:04.014
Thank you.

00:45:06.809 --> 00:45:11.730
The host just gave
such a wonderful introduction

00:45:11.814 --> 00:45:13.607
that I'm honestly overwhelmed.

00:45:14.399 --> 00:45:19.071
I didn't expect so many of you to come,
but thanks to you, filling up the seats,

00:45:19.571 --> 00:45:22.950
I feel like I've become
a best-selling author.

00:45:24.034 --> 00:45:25.536
Call me delusional, but hey.

00:45:25.619 --> 00:45:29.122
I'll work hard to become
a best-selling author, maybe.

00:45:30.541 --> 00:45:32.084
-Right, so today…
-You're here.

00:45:32.167 --> 00:45:34.503
I'd like to extend my heartfelt gratitude…

00:45:34.586 --> 00:45:35.963
Where's Hyeon-suk?

00:45:36.046 --> 00:45:39.633
…to you all for coming all this way
to attend the launch of my book.

00:45:39.716 --> 00:45:42.761
-<i>Designing a Sustainable Future</i>.
-They're not coming today.

00:45:42.845 --> 00:45:45.806
-Something urgent came up.
-I'm truly humbled by your support.

00:45:45.889 --> 00:45:46.849
Thank you so much.

00:45:53.105 --> 00:45:54.773
Why didn't you tell me?

00:45:56.108 --> 00:45:58.819
You should have told me
you were sick sooner.

00:46:00.445 --> 00:46:03.365
I didn't want you to worry.

00:46:05.200 --> 00:46:08.495
I'm okay now. Don't worry.

00:46:08.996 --> 00:46:13.542
Please, how can I not worry?
Do you know how scared I was?

00:46:15.711 --> 00:46:19.256
Please don't get sick anymore, okay?

00:46:20.382 --> 00:46:21.800
Okay.

00:47:21.985 --> 00:47:23.779
<i>I thought everything would be over</i>

00:47:24.279 --> 00:47:26.323
<i>once I buried that secret.</i>

00:47:26.990 --> 00:47:28.241
<i>But it wasn't.</i>

00:47:29.826 --> 00:47:32.996
Yun, what are you doing? Come out here.

00:47:34.289 --> 00:47:35.749
Jeong-hu's leaving.

00:47:54.142 --> 00:47:55.769
What's wrong, Yun?

00:47:59.398 --> 00:48:01.024
Are you not feeling well?

00:48:04.653 --> 00:48:08.073
Are you still upset about
what happened to Min-hui?

00:48:14.663 --> 00:48:16.623
How long are you going to keep this up?

00:48:17.457 --> 00:48:19.418
I have my limits too.

00:48:19.501 --> 00:48:21.670
Get up, Kim Se-yun.

00:48:21.753 --> 00:48:24.464
Now. Listen to your mother!

00:48:27.467 --> 00:48:29.094
They've already had her funeral.

00:48:29.177 --> 00:48:32.389
It's all over. When are you going to
stop acting like a child?

00:48:32.472 --> 00:48:34.766
What do you mean, it's over?

00:48:36.685 --> 00:48:38.437
You have no idea, Mom.

00:48:41.356 --> 00:48:42.816
You don't know.

00:48:43.817 --> 00:48:45.736
You don't know anything.

00:48:45.819 --> 00:48:50.407
<i>That was when it all truly began.</i>

00:48:53.577 --> 00:48:54.911
Oh my God!

00:49:01.501 --> 00:49:02.502
You…

00:49:07.549 --> 00:49:08.842
You were there?

00:49:09.509 --> 00:49:10.635
I saw it.

00:49:12.596 --> 00:49:13.722
I saw everything.

00:49:15.098 --> 00:49:16.767
What Dad did.

00:49:18.018 --> 00:49:19.728
Look, she's bleeding! My God.

00:49:19.811 --> 00:49:21.021
Can you move?

00:49:24.316 --> 00:49:26.943
-She's alive.
-She is.

00:49:30.447 --> 00:49:32.866
Please step aside.

00:49:43.502 --> 00:49:44.669
Please step aside.

00:49:44.753 --> 00:49:46.671
She's unconscious. Oh dear.

00:49:47.964 --> 00:49:49.091
Okay, let's lift her.

00:49:49.174 --> 00:49:50.759
Three, two, lift!

00:49:53.470 --> 00:49:55.222
Three, two, one.

00:49:55.305 --> 00:49:56.598
Let's move.

00:49:57.933 --> 00:49:58.850
<i>Min-hui</i>

00:49:59.434 --> 00:50:03.105
<i>was definitely conscious then.</i>

00:50:20.789 --> 00:50:22.749
Please keep tailing that car.

00:50:37.430 --> 00:50:39.307
Come on, sir.

00:50:53.238 --> 00:50:55.657
She was conscious when brought in.
What happened?

00:50:55.740 --> 00:50:58.285
I'm not sure.
I stepped out for a moment, and…

00:50:58.368 --> 00:51:00.287
-Get ready to perform CPR.
-Will do.

00:51:08.170 --> 00:51:10.255
-Please page the clinical fellow.
-Sure.

00:51:11.214 --> 00:51:13.049
No pulse. She's in cardiac arrest.

00:51:13.133 --> 00:51:14.759
Start compressions. Now.

00:51:14.843 --> 00:51:16.761
Starting compressions, now!

00:51:33.028 --> 00:51:34.779
-Epinephrine every three minutes.
-Yes.

00:51:35.363 --> 00:51:37.949
-Intubate her as soon as we're ready.
-Understood.

00:52:04.184 --> 00:52:05.101
So…

00:52:08.355 --> 00:52:10.232
So, your housekeeper…

00:52:11.733 --> 00:52:13.193
With your own two hands…

00:52:25.747 --> 00:52:27.123
No, Yun.

00:52:29.709 --> 00:52:31.127
Not yet.

00:52:33.213 --> 00:52:34.673
Nothing is certain.

00:52:34.756 --> 00:52:38.093
No, it was Dad's car.
It was definitely Dad!

00:52:40.220 --> 00:52:42.347
Dad did something to her.

00:52:46.226 --> 00:52:47.227
My baby.

00:52:52.148 --> 00:52:53.858
I hoped you'd never find out.

00:53:02.742 --> 00:53:03.618
Mom.

00:53:05.370 --> 00:53:06.705
How did you…

00:53:10.292 --> 00:53:11.751
How long have you known?

00:53:15.588 --> 00:53:16.548
Yun.

00:53:18.008 --> 00:53:20.135
That's not important right now.

00:53:21.803 --> 00:53:24.180
Stop crying and listen to me.

00:53:25.223 --> 00:53:27.809
We now have to find out

00:53:28.435 --> 00:53:29.436
what Dad really did…

00:53:31.313 --> 00:53:33.106
for ourselves.

00:53:36.151 --> 00:53:37.277
How?

00:53:45.618 --> 00:53:49.873
How about we go see a late-night movie
after this? It's been a while.

00:53:50.874 --> 00:53:52.000
A late-night movie?

00:53:53.418 --> 00:53:55.170
Or we could just go for a drive.

00:53:56.212 --> 00:53:57.505
Doesn't that sound wonderful?

00:53:57.589 --> 00:53:59.966
It'd be a waste to stay home
on a night like this.

00:54:00.050 --> 00:54:03.720
No, I can't. I have plans,
so I have to go out in a bit.

00:54:13.021 --> 00:54:16.358
You go to the hospital.
I'll go to the park.

00:54:16.441 --> 00:54:18.193
When I meet your dad there,

00:54:18.943 --> 00:54:21.196
I'm going to question him
about everything.

00:54:22.155 --> 00:54:26.576
In the meantime, you have to check
the hospital's CCTV footage.

00:54:27.619 --> 00:54:28.620
Got it?

00:55:10.954 --> 00:55:13.373
Hey, Jeong-hu.
Why are you calling me so late?

00:55:13.873 --> 00:55:14.833
What?

00:55:17.001 --> 00:55:19.379
Yun knows everything? What does he know?

00:55:23.007 --> 00:55:23.967
Jeong-hu.

00:55:24.676 --> 00:55:27.095
I have no idea what you're talking about.

00:55:27.679 --> 00:55:28.930
Let's meet up first.

00:55:29.973 --> 00:55:31.307
Let's talk in person.

00:55:57.459 --> 00:55:58.501
Hey, Yun.

00:55:59.461 --> 00:56:00.336
Did you find it?

00:56:00.837 --> 00:56:01.963
Did you check it?

00:56:14.976 --> 00:56:15.810
Se-yun.

00:56:21.983 --> 00:56:24.027
<i>Yun was crying.</i>

00:56:25.653 --> 00:56:27.655
He said the footage was useless.

00:56:30.366 --> 00:56:33.328
It was in a blind spot,
so he couldn't see anything.

00:56:38.583 --> 00:56:40.960
It's over now. It's all over.

00:56:41.753 --> 00:56:45.673
We lost all the evidence we could've used
to get a confession out of him.

00:56:48.885 --> 00:56:50.345
This is all my fault.

00:56:51.179 --> 00:56:53.389
I shouldn't have gotten rid of that file.

00:56:56.184 --> 00:56:58.811
I don't know how I'll face him
from now on.

00:57:01.856 --> 00:57:03.650
It's so scary, so horrifying.

00:57:11.324 --> 00:57:12.992
I don't know what to do now.

00:57:16.287 --> 00:57:19.207
How am I meant to go on living?

00:57:28.466 --> 00:57:29.509
Eun-joo.

00:57:32.470 --> 00:57:33.346
It's okay.

00:57:37.183 --> 00:57:38.434
I'll help you.

00:57:40.353 --> 00:57:41.771
I'll do whatever it takes.

00:57:50.488 --> 00:57:51.739
Don't worry.

00:58:05.336 --> 00:58:10.466
MR. HEO MUN-OH

00:58:26.149 --> 00:58:26.983
Lee Kang.

00:58:28.318 --> 00:58:29.402
Listen carefully.

00:58:30.069 --> 00:58:31.279
That evidence.

00:58:32.322 --> 00:58:33.865
We can make it ourselves.

00:58:35.867 --> 00:58:37.035
What do you mean by--

00:58:37.118 --> 00:58:39.245
<i>Just listen to me, you punk!</i>

00:58:41.247 --> 00:58:44.500
That night,
the night of Seon Min-hui's accident.

00:58:45.043 --> 00:58:47.545
You followed her to the hospital, okay?

00:58:48.129 --> 00:58:50.340
You followed Kim Su-hun to the hospital.

00:58:51.841 --> 00:58:52.675
What?

00:58:52.759 --> 00:58:54.010
And there,

00:58:55.053 --> 00:58:56.471
you witnessed it.

00:59:17.075 --> 00:59:19.619
You saw it with your own two eyes.

00:59:20.203 --> 00:59:21.454
Do you understand me?

00:59:22.455 --> 00:59:23.581
<i>Mr. Heo.</i>

00:59:24.666 --> 00:59:26.376
That will be how…

00:59:28.461 --> 00:59:30.088
your story ends.

00:59:34.509 --> 00:59:37.512
NOTES FROM THE LAST ROW

01:02:03.616 --> 01:02:08.621
Subtitle translation by: Jimin Choi